  "text": "(F) Validation of PPP1R17 as a marker for an amacrine subpopulation. Staining of a fixed adult retina from Mito-P mice, which express CFP in both nGnG amacrines and type 1 bipolars [CITATION_1] . Overlapping labeling by PPP1R17 antibody (green) and Mito-P CFP (red) supports Drop-seq identification of Ppp1r17 expression in the nGnG amacrine neurons. 85% of CFP+ cells were PPP1R17+ and 50% of the PPP1R17+ cells were CFPÀ, suggesting a second amacrine type expressing this marker. Blue staining is for VSX2, a marker of bipolar neurons.",
